column3: @fanquake This should be removed as soon as it's created: https://github.com/fanquake/bitcoin/blob/c52c0cdc8964d506e083d7cbc4fe6514f7398175/src/Makefile.qt.include#L430\n\nAny idea what's keeping it around for you?
I don't think it hurts to add it to CLEANFILES just in case, but yes that is weird.

Sure, adding it as a backup is fine. It'd just be helpful to know why it's sticking around, as I'm not sure how that could happen.\n\n@fanquake Mind changing this to CLEAN_QT in Makefile.qt.include instead? utACK after that.

@theuni Rebased and updated to use CLEAN_QT

Still not sure what is making it hang around. Maybe permissions related?
```
  GEN      qt/qrc_bitcoin_locale.cpp
override r--r--r--  xxx/staff for qt/temp_bitcoin_locale.qrc? 
``

@fanquake ah yes, that must be it. distcheck makes all files read-only, I guess the parent dir ends up with a umask set.\n\nThere's a cleaner way to handle this using the ```.INTERMEDIATE``` target, but it's not really worth the effort here.
